div.p:
Object. 5. If Adam fell the ninth houre of the ſixth day;

   Pag. 25. 
how did God in the end of that day ſee all his workes to be very good?

But it may here be objected, God threatned to viſit the ſinnes of the Fathers upon the Children but unto the third and fourth generation of them that hate him; 
                     Object. 
                   therefore this viſitation could not be ſo large, as throughout all theſe precedent generations.
